catalog.title: Marathon Lasagna
catalog.notes: This is a double recipe, 1x to eat, 1x to freeze (instead of cook). BUY: 1 container parmesan cheese, 24oz spinach (2 bags or 5 containers), 4 lg yams, 2 boxes no-boil lasagna, 4 jars marinara, 3lbs turkey, 4 eggs, 1 bag mozz cheese, 1x 32-oz ricotta. RECIPE: peel yams, IP 10+0. Heat oil, saute garlic/turkey/oregano/fennel/redPepper/salt, add red sauce, wilt spinach. Mash yams w/ butter/salt/pepper/4eggs/ricotta. COMBINE: sauce. Noodles/sauce/potatoes/mozz. Repeat until full, add parmesan.

catalog.title: IP pot roast
catalog.notes: BUY: This is a double recipe: makes 8 servings. BUY: onion, baby carrots, 4lb potatoes, 1 can beef broth, 1 packet onion gravy/soup mix, 1 bag corn, 4lb roast. RECIPE: cut roast into large cubes, dry rub salt/pepper/onionPowder/garlicPowder. IP saute in oil. Remove, scrape bits using a little beef broth. Add garlic, then onions and the rest of beef broth. Add beef back in, cover with onion packet. Add quartered potatoes, cook 75+20. Remove potatoes & beef. Add carrots, 0+0. Meanwhile, blend mashed potatoes with butter/milk. Shred beef. When IP finishes, whisk 2+2tbsp cornstarch slurry, then add frozen corn to cool. Layer: mashed potatoes, beef, sauce!

catalog.title: Asparagus-stuffed chicken
catalog.notes: Family pack of chicken. Butterfly, then pound really flat. 1 bundle of asparagus, plenty of provolone. Use toothpicks to secure. Pan sear, set aside. Cast iron 1.5c chicken broth + 1can condensed cream of chicken. Add chicken, cover, bake to 160 then remove so it can reach 165. Serve over 1lb pasta, i.e. linguine or thin spaghetti. Or quinoa.

catalog.title: Chipotle chicken burritos

catalog.notes: Single batch is kind of small. 1.5x batch is ideal, 2x for XL (this size: family pack chicken breast, 5lb potatoes). Not as much wine, maybe half recommended amount. Pound chicken a little for even cooking. Cook carrots in 2nd round for 2min.

catalog.title: Ham & Navy Bean Soup
catalog.notes: Carve full ham, freeze half. Soak beans. IP ham hock, 7c water, 5 bay leaves, diced onion, 45+15. Remove hock and bay leaves. Add beans and diced ham, 15+5. Add sliced carrots, celery, diced potatoes, jarlic, paprika, pepper, rosemary, 5+0. Add splash apple cider vinegar, frozen corn.

catalog.title: IP chicken fajitas

catalog.title: Beef Plov
catalog.notes: Sauté cubed/seasoned beef chuck. 4tbsp butter. Lots of half sliced baby carrots, seasoned salt, pepper, paprika, cumin, coriander. Evenly top with 2.5c rice, don't stir. Push 1-2 cross-cut garlic bulbs into rice. Top with 3c hot water. 30+10.

catalog.title: IP Chicken Curry
catalog.notes: Sauté 8-9 seasoned chicken thighs, set aside. Sauté butter, onion, ginger, tomato sauce (paste too thick = burns),  curry powder, cayenne. Add chicken stock, deglaze, 2c total. Add soy sauce, chicken, whole bag baby carrots, 2.5lb diced potatoes. 8+10. Goes well with 2.5c white rice (not enough room for PIP).
